<paper id="1600297185"><title>Monotone Expansion of Updates in Logical Databases</title><year>1999</year><authors><author org="Tver State University," id="1271351648">Michael I. Dekhtyar</author><author org="Universite De Nantes" id="2143690299">Alexander Ja. Dikovsky</author><author org="Tver State University," id="2001412195">Sergey Dudakov</author><author org="Université de Paris-Sud - LRI" id="171306905">Nicolas Spyratos</author></authors><n_citation>6</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>29574133</reference><reference>61634967</reference><reference>176609766</reference><reference>1519659352</reference><reference>1551212655</reference><reference>1561370784</reference><reference>1589487547</reference><reference>1593260998</reference><reference>1846779381</reference><reference>1982345710</reference><reference>1986329319</reference><reference>1995080554</reference><reference>2094341147</reference></references><venue id="1201110412" type="C">International Conference on Logic Programming</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-46767-X_10</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.49488">Program optimization</keyword><keyword weight="0.41095">Information system</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Logic program</keyword><keyword weight="0.46867">Negation</keyword><keyword weight="0.45207">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.46055">Algorithm</keyword><keyword weight="0.46588">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.50596">Data integrity</keyword><keyword weight="0.48455">Circumscription</keyword><keyword weight="0.51466">Operator (computer programming)</keyword><keyword weight="0.54592">Monotone polygon</keyword><keyword weight="0.42142">Database</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>To find a minimal real change after an update of a database with integrity constraints (IC) expressed by a generalized logic program with explicit negation is proven to be a Σ2p-complete problem. We define a class of operators expanding the input updates correctly with respect to the IC. The particular monotone expansion operator we describe is incrementally computed in square time. It provides a practical optimization of the standard complete choice algorithm resolving the update problem.</abstract></paper>